column2:
This was by far the most bizarre issue I have ever seen the left freak out about. I mean they were screaming about the most absurd things and none of them took a step back and thought, "well now wait a minute, all these shady corporations like Google and Amazon are in favor of net neutrality....I wonder why that would be? Maybe I should look this up myself"

&#x200B;

And to make it more ridiculous most of the people who I talked to that were for "net neutrality" didn't understand what it was at all.....believe me, I asked

&#x200B;

I will give them this though....it was the most successful astroturfing campaign I have ever seen

column109:
you'd think those people would spend 15 minutes looking up what it actually is rather than just taking Google and Reddit's word for it lol.

&#x200B;

I can guarantee you there are still people all over T\_D that bought into their propaganda and still think net neutrality was a good thing

column133:
